<div id="review_319868440" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/319868440" />
    <a title="Michelle" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1200378-michelle"><img alt="Michelle" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1212204577p2/1200378.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/319868440?book_show_action=true">Apr 27, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michelle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michelle" href="/user/show/1200378-michelle">Michelle</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer319868440" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11371084467389750432">This is an important book. It&apos;s just not especially well-written. Normally, with this weighty a topic I&apos;d be more forgiving but I found the writing was annoying enough to really affect my ability to concentrate on what most mattered...that it is a horrific practice which allows for prepubescent little girls to be married off to men 3 or more times their age. Obviously, an illiterate 10 year old girl is going to need the assistance of a co-author. And I applaud Ms. Minoui for taking this on. Firs</span>
  <span id="freeText11371084467389750432" style="display:none">This is an important book. It's just not especially well-written. Normally, with this weighty a topic I'd be more forgiving but I found the writing was annoying enough to really affect my ability to concentrate on what most mattered...that it is a horrific practice which allows for prepubescent little girls to be married off to men 3 or more times their age. Obviously, an illiterate 10 year old girl is going to need the assistance of a co-author. And I applaud Ms. Minoui for taking this on. First person is an obvious choice here for the voice. Just because a child is illiterate doesn't preclude eloquence but when the author starts using words like coquettish it just comes across as false and overly flowery. I wouldn't want it to read like a Dick and Jane primer but the voice given Ali seemed uneven at best, inauthentic at worst. <br /><br />Criticism aside, I'd urge folks to read this because it's an eye-opener. There aren't excuses made for the practice of a family marrying off a child but there is a presentation of the complexity of the issue through one family's story which allows for an understanding of how this can continue to happen in the 21st century. It's a horrific practice with no redeeming quality to be sure. The young Ms. Ali is truly a remarkable girl for having found the strength to demand and win her liberation when no adult in her world would stand up for her before the day when she walked into a courthouse in Sana'a. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11371084467389750432" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


